MyJersey project is created so we can quickly prototype Jersey base REST API.

To server to purpose of variety of consumers (web, mobile), RESTful APIs and standardize 
message encoding is a must. Jersey based REST API and JSON encoded message like good choice.

The prototype system setup:
1. setup mongodb:
   . download mongodb-osx-x86_64-3.0.3.tar
   . <untar it>
   . <create the mongo data directory {/path/to/mongoData}>
   . mongod --dbpath {/path/to/mongoData}
2. MyJersey project cant be run out of Jetty:
   mvn clean install jetty:run
3. MyJersey contains the Prototypes and test, as listed in section AsOf20150525.
4. also a sample Java program under src/test/java, RESTClient.java for prototyping consuming REST in java.    
   
   
Prototype List:
AsOf20150525
------------
API					Test
----				-----
/userCreatex		http://localhost:8080/MyJersey/addUserForm.html
/userQueryx			http://localhost:8080/MyJersey/rest/userQueryx
/userLoginx			http://localhost:8080/MyJersey/loginUserForm.html
/userQueryx/{email}	http://localhost:8080/MyJersey/rest/userQueryx/<substr in your email>